<body>
	
<header>
	See if you can remember some things about the speaking section of the IELTS exam.Which of the following statements are true and which are false?
</header>
	
<section id="body">
	<img class="rightFloat" src="../Media/TT_SP_003.jpg" mode="1" id="1001"  /><br/><ol id="questionList"><br/><li id="1">The examiner asks all candidates the same questions. <br/></li><font face="verdana" size="13" color="#0f157a"><b><a id="q1" >True</a><tab/><a id="q2" >False</a></b></font><br/><li id="2">The candidate has to state his or her full name. <a id="q3" >True</a><tab/><a id="q4" >False</a><br/></li><br/><li id="3">All three parts of the test are connected to each other. <a id="q5" >True</a><tab/><a id="q6" >False</a><br/></li><br/><li id="4">The candidate talks on his or her own about a topic of his choice. <a id="q7" >True</a><tab/><a id="q8" >False</a><br/></li><br/><li id="5">The examiner introduces herself to the candidate. <a id="q9" >True</a><tab/><a id="q10" >False</a><br/></li><br/><li id="6">The candidate has to produce identification. <a id="q11" >True</a><tab/><a id="q12" >False</a><br/></li><br/><li id="7">The candidate has a turn to ask questions. <a id="q13" >True</a><tab/><a id="q14" >False</a><br/></li></ol>
</section>
<section id="fb1">
	<p align="left">There are several different exam packs examiners can use and each has a variety of questions to choose from.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb2">
	<p align="left">Your name is needed for identification.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb3">
	<p align="left">Only Parts 2 and 3 are connected.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb4">
	<p align="left">The examiner will give you the topic to talk about.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb5">
	<p align="left">Examiners will introduce themselves.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb6">
	<p align="left">Without identification you will not be allowed to take the exam.</p>
</section>
<section id="fb7">
	<p align="left">The candidate can ask for a question to be repeated or clarified but nothing else.</p>
</section>
